| media-library-access | critical | not-applicable | Media library and album discovery |  |\n250: | background-and-platform-components | high | not-applicable | Background work, services, receivers, widgets, and notifications |  |\n251: | runtime-permissions | high | not-applicable | Runtime permissions and protected platform access |  |\n252: \n253: ## Instructions\n254: \n255: - Start with implementationGroups as the current phase implementation contract: implement each group, then use mustComplete entries as exact row-level checks.\n256: - Use planContract as upstream planning ownership evidence; resolve its alignmentFindings by updating plannedPhase/matrix/platform evidence or by documenting sourceOverride/analysisGap when source inspection disagrees.\n257: - Keep grouped business behavior discoverable through precise target endpoints; avoid closing unrelated features only through root/shell/whole-file endpoints.\n258: - Merge source files only when it improves target clarity and still preserves per-feature evidence, tests, and controllable file size.\n259: - Treat mustComplete entries as the current phase's executable row-level task list.\n260: - Use behaviorAudit as the current phase behavior audit; it checks closed critical/high rows for source behavior, target behavior, parity, and verification evidence.\n261: - Use uiContract entries as static-analysis planning aids, not complete UI specifications: preserve listed source-visible screen structure, route/back behavior, actions, state feedback, and visual evidence needs, then re-read source/resources/navigation for UI behavior the static analysis may have missed.\n262: - Do not close the phase while current-phase critical/high entries are open, weakly deferred, or missing evidence.\n263: - For every closed critical/high source feature, record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence in source-coverage-matrix.json.\n264: - A build pass alone is not per-feature verification; cite tests, manual/emulator evidence, or explicit verificationEvidence for behavior closure.\n265: - Use implemented-simplified only with concrete simplification reason, preserved-behavior explanation, target endpoints or tests, and source/platform evidence.\n266: - If a suitable HarmonyOS/Cangjie API, Kit, example, or package exists for a platform capability, use it or record a platform replacement; do not close the item with local mock data, sample data, in-memory simulation, or another fallback.\n267: - Use deferred only for concrete blockers; otherwise implement faithfully or platform-replace with evidence.\n268: - Update source-coverage-matrix.json/md and platform-capability-check.json/md before phase completion.\n269: - If this checklist is empty but the phase has real scope in plan.md/plan.json, assign plannedPhase values first.\n\n(End of file - total 269 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Phase Task Checklist\n\n- Phase: `phase-04-home-history-discovery`\n\n## Purpose\n\nCurrent-phase task checklist generated from the agent-maintained source coverage matrix and platform capability check. Use it before editing and update the matrix/check after work.\n\n## Summary\n\n| metric | value |\n| --- | --- |\n| phaseFeatureEntries | 30 |\n| phaseCriticalHighFeatureEntries | 26 |\n| mustCompleteFeatureEntries | 26 |\n| needsEvidenceFeatureEntries | 0 |\n| deferredOrFallbackFeatureEntries | 0 |\n| coveredFeatureEntries | 0 |\n| phaseSourceFiles | 9 |\n| phasePlatformCapabilityEntries | 0 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\phase-task-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782389069915,"end":1782389069926}},"id":"prt_efeaad84f001bM1xA7OZmKU6Wh","sessionID":"ses_1015564daffeewn8Ynq2E7YoiC","messageID":"msg_efeaac5e8001573AvtCf3lBnKU"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1782389070197,"sessionID":"ses_1015564daffeewn8Ynq2E7YoiC","part":{"id":"prt_efeaad973001BXugRfd8ac6w0f","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"0e2e8fb6fc195aaecf459fa1fd98a6bf54585599","messageID":"msg_efeaac5e8001573AvtCf3lBnKU","sessionID":"ses_1015564daffeewn8Ynq2E7YoiC","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":16911,"input":16652,"output":259,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":0}},"cost":0}}
