{"type":"text","timestamp":1782394228739,"sessionID":"ses_1015564daffeewn8Ynq2E7YoiC","part":{"id":"prt_efef97a9f001H03PbZqOfty6tI","messageID":"msg_efecbe2d00011sDURTRwunsiV9","sessionID":"ses_1015564daffeewn8Ynq2E7YoiC","type":"text","text":"I want to keep home/history-specific observable state out of the shell if possible, so I’m checking one more ArkUI pattern: how this SDK instantiates a custom `@Component` from another builder. If it’s straightforward, I’ll isolate the page state there; otherwise I’ll use the bootstrap shell only for the minimal route-local fields.","time":{"start":1782394223263,"end":1782394228738}}}
